  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Zambia Disability Platform</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To contribute towards achieving a Zambian society in which disabled persons enjoy full participation in National Development with all their fundamental rights and freedoms guaranteed by 2015 
1. To create a unified platform for the disability movement to advocate for the domestication of the UNCRPD.
2. To develop a common advocacy agenda for the disability movement
3. To strengthen institutional capacity of Disability and Blind people&#x2019;s organisations.
4. To develop the advocacy skills of persons with disabilities by 2013 
Some key activities
&#x2022; Create a platform for joint advocacy and capacity building for DPOs/BPOs
&#x2022; Lobby for increased funding to the disability sector.
&#x2022; develop appropriate strategy to address inadequacies
&#x2022; strengthen capacity of government funded DPOs in organisational development and programme delivery
&#x2022; Train persons with disabilities in self advocacy skills
&#x2022; Engage donors, private, public and social sectors to include disability issues in their policies and programmes.
&#x2022; Conduct sensitisation activities for parents and guardians on the importance of educating persons with disability</narrative>
  </description>
